Privacy Policy for Discord Support Bot
Last updated: [Datum einsetzen]

1. Introduction
This Privacy Policy explains how information is collected, used, and protected when using the Discord Support Bot (“the Bot”) and related Client software (“the Client”).

2. Information We Collect
Hardware ID (HWID): Used to uniquely identify client devices for support purposes.

Username: The operating system username of the client device user.

IP Address: Collected during device registration to help identify the device location.

Command Logs and Status Updates: Commands sent to clients and their execution results are logged and sent to your Discord server channels.

3. How We Use Your Information
To identify and manage client devices within the support system.

To deliver commands from support staff to the correct client devices.

To provide status updates and logs to authorized support personnel via Discord.

4. Data Sharing and Disclosure
Your data is stored and used only within the scope of providing support via the Bot and Client.

Data is shared only with authorized support staff who have access to your Discord server.

We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information.

5. Data Security
Reasonable measures are taken to protect your data from unauthorized access or disclosure.

However, no system can guarantee 100% security.

6. Data Retention
Device registrations, command logs, and status updates are retained as long as necessary to provide support services.

7. User Rights
You have the right to request deletion or modification of your device data by contacting the support team.

You are responsible for securing your Discord account and server access.

8. Changes to This Policy
This Privacy Policy may be updated occasionally. Continued use of the Bot and Client constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.

9. Contact
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact the developer.

